<br>
I can not imagine another company doing a better job then they are.  I mean, I guess if they spent more time player testing there might be fewer bugs/issues, but then we would have to wait longer to be able to play it.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think most of the issues many people have trying to just install or get into SOL, are problems not directly related to Sol but rather having the correct Driver or system Requirements to play.<br>
<br>
So sure they did raise the bar, which is frustrating to those who need to upgrade, but the SOL product is damn good, as is EQ as a whole.  I don't know any other game out there with this much content and detail that has fewer bugs/issues.<br>
<br>
In my opinion too many things get thrown into the category of bugs or issues with the game that were either designed that way or are not related to the actual games software.  I am not denying the presence of actual bugs or issues that need to be resolved, I am just defending Verant, as I at least have respect for the product they have created and one which they continue to perfect.  (I am not saying it's perfect but its better then any other game I have seen with as much content and detail)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
